{
  "texts": [
    "He shows examples of made-up references, made up authors and made-up research articles.",
    "The attentive, and knowledgeable, reader will pick up on this, but what if you don't?This brings me to the first ethical implication: the generation of content.",
    "To some, the use of GenAI might be comparable to using Google Translate, Microsoft's Word proofing or any other (paid) service to improve your writing.",
    "However, GenAI is much more powerful than these tools, because it does not just improve your spelling and grammar, it generates content.",
    "One might ask how that is any different from searching through literature on Google Scholar or Web of Science, but the difference is that GenAI is not transparent about where the information is sourced and it is near impossible to uncover."
  ]
}